      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I don't believe there is a biological or genetic link between race and crime — it's all about the societal structures and policies that unfairly target certain racial groups. The stereotypes about inherent criminal propensities and innate antisocial behaviors are misconceptions based on biased perceptions. The truth is that those systemic inequities, like concentrated poverty and racial profiling, perpetuate the illusion of a genetic predisposition to crime. Different racial groups are overrepresented in the prison system because of historical and ongoing discrimination, not because of any biological differences.",
